SENATE BILL 743
R5 6lr3349
By: Senator James
Introduced and read first time: February 6, 2026
Assigned to: Judicial Proceedings
A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Workgroup to Study State Laws on Electric Bicycles – Establishment
3 FOR the purpose of establishing the Workgroup to Study State Laws on Electric Bicycles
4 to study current State laws on electric bicycles; and generally relating to the
5 Workgroup to Study State Laws on Electric Bicycles.
6 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
7 That:
8 (a) There is a Workgroup to Study State Laws on Electric Bicycles.
9 (b) The Workgroup consists of the following members:
10 (1) one member of the Senate of Maryland, appointed by the President of
11 the Senate;
12 (2) one member of the House of Delegates, appointed by the Speaker of the
13 House;
14 (3) the Secretary of Transportation, or the Secretary’s designee;
15 (4) the Secretary of State Police, or the Secretary’s designee;
16 (5) the President of the Maryland Association of Counties, or the
17 President’s designee;
18 (6) the President of the Maryland Municipal League, or the President’s
19 designee; and
20 (7) the following members, appointed by the Governor:
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
[Brackets] indicate matter deleted from exist in g l aw . *sb0743*

2 SENATE BILL 743
1 (i) one representative of a rural law enforcement agency;
2 (ii) one representative of a suburban law enforcement agency; and
3 (iii) one representative of an urban law enforcement agency.
4 (c) The Workgroup shall elect a chair from among its members.
5 (d) The Department of Transportation shall provide staff for the Workgroup.
6 (e) A member of the Workgroup:
7 (1) may not receive compensation as a member of the Workgroup; but
8 (2) is entitled to reimbursement for expenses under the Standard State
9 Travel Regulations, as provided in the State budget.
10 (f) The Workgroup shall:
11 (1) review current State law regarding rules of the road for electric bicycles
12 and make recommendations for revisions to improve public safety and address safety
13 concerns identified during the study;
14 (2) review information from academic studies and data compiled by
15 governments on injury rates and general safety concerns of electric bicycle riders and, to
16 the extent they are impacted by the use of electric bicycles, other vehicle operators and
17 pedestrians; and
18 (3) consider the significance and role of other micro–mobility devices with
19 respect to public safety.
20 (g) On or before January 1, 2028, the Workgroup shall report its findings and
21 recommendations to the Governor and, in accordance with § 2–1257 of the State
22 Government Article, the General Assembly.
23 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
24 1, 2026. It shall remain effective for a period of 1 year and 6 months and, at the end of
25 January 1, 2028, this Act, with no further action required by the General Assembly, shall
26 be abrogated and of no further force and effect.

